{
 "name": "RPlog_SW1_Log_2000-08-08-2",
 "title": "Touring the Moisture Farm",
 "summary": "On Tatooine, the Intelligence officer Kathryn Jrevelian welcomes the acting director, Bazil McKenzie, to a secret NRI facility disguised as a moisture farm buried in the Dune Sea. Shaking off the sand, Bazil -- who grew up on the harsh world -- marvels at the lavish, well-appointed compound housing comms, an arsenal, quarters, and a hidden garage. Kathryn proudly details its defenses: eight domes concealing heavy quad-laser cannons, sixteen illegal Gladiator X5 assassin droids, and a self-destruct system that can sink and destroy the whole structure. The two trade easy banter about whiskey, uplinks, and the strategic value of a Tatooine foothold should the Empire reclaim the planet, before Kathryn turns in for the night and Bazil lingers at a terminal, quietly zooming the night-sky display in on a lone asteroid at the system's edge.",
